3. Gaps & Missing Pieces (What It Needs)

🔴 Critical Issues

Issue	File	Severity	Description	
BIP-39 Entropy Bug	`bip39Helper.js:22`	🔴 CRITICAL	`entropyToMnemonic` receives a hex string concatenation of random bytes, not the raw bytes. `bip39.entropyToMnemonic()` expects a Buffer/Uint8Array or hex string of correct length. The current implementation: `Array.from(entropy).map(b => b.toString(16).padStart(2, '0')).join('')` produces a hex string like `"a3f7..."` which is then passed to `entropyToMnemonic`. If the entropy is 16 bytes, this creates a 32-char hex string. The function interprets this as 16 bytes of hex, not 16 bytes of entropy. This may produce valid but non-standard mnemonics with reduced entropy space.	
Bitcoin Derivation Path Wrong	`bip39Helper.js:45`	🔴 CRITICAL	Uses `m/44'/0'/0'/0/0` (legacy P2PKH) instead of modern `m/84'/0'/0'/0/0` (SegWit/bech32) or `m/49'/0'/0'/0/0` (P2SH-SegWit). For a 2026 tool, this generates legacy addresses starting with `1` instead of `bc1q`. Users will lose funds if they expect modern Bitcoin addresses.	
Solana Key Derivation Broken	`bip39Helper.js:68`	🔴 CRITICAL	Derives Solana via `bip32` (secp256k1-based) then feeds the private key into `nacl.sign.keyPair.fromSecretKey()`. Solana uses Ed25519, not secp256k1. BIP-32 hierarchical derivation with secp256k1 curve points fed into Ed25519 is cryptographically invalid. The derived secret key is 32 bytes but was derived via the wrong curve. This will generate unrecoverable Solana addresses — funds sent to these addresses would be lost.	
CREATE2 Implementation Incomplete	`create2.js`	🔴 HIGH	File cuts off mid-implementation (`@returns {Promise`). The vanity salt brute-forcer is not fully implemented in the retrieved source.	
Rate Limiting Logic Bug	`useAddressGenerator.js:76`	🔴 HIGH	`attemptsRef.current += 1000` hardcodes 1000 attempts per stats message, but worker sends stats every 10,000 attempts. The main thread undercounts by 10x, making speed calculations and ETA wildly inaccurate.	

🟡 Important Issues

Issue	File	Severity	Description	
No Test Suite	Entire project	🟡 HIGH	`package.json` lists `vitest` and `@testing-library/react` as devDeps, but no test files exist. Zero unit tests for crypto functions, zero integration tests for worker communication, zero e2e tests despite Playwright being configured.	
No TypeScript	Entire project	🟡 MEDIUM	All `.js/.jsx` files. Crypto code especially benefits from type safety (buffer vs string confusion caused the BIP-39 bug).	
Wordlist Quality Concerns	`wordlists.js`	🟡 MEDIUM	Theme wordlists are padded with repetitive nonsense words (e.g., 100+ "bandarloggreen" variants, 200+ "bulletproof" in food theme). The "food" theme contains "bulletproof" 200+ times. This defeats the purpose of a 2048-word cipher — low entropy per word, easily guessable.	
Missing SUI/Cosmos/Aptos Derivation	`bip39Helper.js`	🟡 MEDIUM	`getAllAddresses()` only returns ETH, BTC, SOL. SUI, Cosmos, Aptos derivation exists in `chainCrypto.js` but not in the HD wallet helper.	
No Input Validation on Password	`encryption.js`	🟡 MEDIUM	`encryptPrivateKey()` accepts any password without length/strength validation. Weak passwords silently accepted.	
Clipboard "Zeroize" is Theater	`useCloakSeed.js:186`	🟡 MEDIUM	`navigator.clipboard.writeText('[CLEARED]')` does not actually clear system clipboard history. macOS, Windows, and Linux clipboard managers retain history. The warning console log is the only real protection.	
Missing Worker Error Recovery	`generatorWorker.js`	🟡 MEDIUM	Worker errors are caught and logged but generation continues. A corrupted worker could spin indefinitely without the user knowing.	
No Memory Pressure Handling	`useAddressGenerator.js`	🟡 MEDIUM	No `performance.memory` checks or `WeakRef` usage. Long-running generation with many results could OOM the tab.	

