6. Code Quality & Maintainability

Structure Assessment

```
src/
├── components/     # 12 JSX components — mostly functional, some incomplete
├── hooks/          # 3 custom hooks — good abstraction
├── workers/        # 1 worker — clean but basic
├── utils/          # 11 utility modules — mixed quality
```

TypeScript & Type Safety
- Status: ❌ Not used (pure JS)
- Impact: The BIP-39 entropy bug (string vs Buffer confusion) would have been caught by TypeScript
- Recommendation: Migrate to TypeScript immediately. The crypto domain especially benefits from strict typing.

Error Handling
- Workers have `try/catch` but errors are only `console.error`'d and messaged to main thread
- No retry logic for crypto operations
- No graceful degradation if Web Workers are unavailable (Safari iOS private mode)
- `useAddressGenerator` has basic error state but no error boundaries in React

Duplication
- `hexToBytes`, `bytesToHex` duplicated in `crypto.js`, `chainCrypto.js`, `create2.js`, `encryption.js`, `ciphers.js`, `profiles.js` (6+ copies)
- `toChecksumAddress` duplicated in `crypto.js` and `chainCrypto.js`
- Base64 helpers duplicated in `encryption.js`, `ciphers.js`, `profiles.js`

Test Coverage
- 0% — No tests exist despite vitest + Playwright in devDependencies
- No property-based testing for crypto (e.g., `fast-check` for round-trip BIP-39)
- No worker integration tests
- No UI component tests

CI/CD
- No `.github/workflows` visible in retrieved files
- No linting configuration retrieved (ESLint referenced in package.json)
- No automated security scanning (Dependabot, Snyk)

